Kuwait, whose shipping has come underrepeated attack by Iran, has the full support of Saudi Arabiaand other Gulf allies, a senior government official said.    Cabinet spokesman Abdul-Aziz al-Otaibi, quoted by theKuwaiti news agency KUNA yesterday, said Foreign MinisterSheikh Sabah al-Ahmed al-Sabah had told cabinet he had found"complete support...At this delicate phase" during visits to GulfCooperation Council (GCC) states.    The GCC, an economic and military alliance which hasgenerally supported Iraq over Iran, comprises Bahrain, Kuwait,Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates. REUTER&#3;